import json 
from urllib.request import urlopen

world2_url = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/world-atlas@2/countries-110m.json'

world2 = json.load(urlopen(world2_url))
print(type(world2))
print(world2.keys())

print(world2['objects']['countries'].keys())
print(world2['objects']['countries']['geometries'][0])

Code 
import pandas as pd
import altair as alt
from vega_datasets import data

states_geojson = alt.topo_feature(data.us_10m.url, 'states')
airports_df = data.airports()

state_abbrev_to_name = {
    "AL": "Alabama",
    "AK": "Alaska",
    "AZ": "Arizona",
    "AR": "Arkansas",
    "CA": "California",
    "CO": "Colorado",
    "CT": "Connecticut",
    "DE": "Delaware",
    "DC": "District of Columbia",
    "FL": "Florida",
    "GA": "Georgia",
    "HI": "Hawaii",
    "ID": "Idaho",
    "IL": "Illinois",
    "IN": "Indiana",
    "IA": "Iowa",
    "KS": "Kansas",
    "KY": "Kentucky",
    "LA": "Louisiana",
    "ME": "Maine",
    "MT": "Montana",
    "NE": "Nebraska",
    "NV": "Nevada",
    "NH": "New Hampshire",
    "NJ": "New Jersey",
    "NM": "New Mexico",
    "NY": "New York",
    "NC": "North Carolina",
    "ND": "North Dakota",
    "OH": "Ohio",
    "OK": "Oklahoma",
    "OR": "Oregon",
    "MD": "Maryland",
    "MA": "Massachusetts",
    "MI": "Michigan",
    "MN": "Minnesota",
    "MS": "Mississippi",
    "MO": "Missouri",
    "PA": "Pennsylvania",
    "RI": "Rhode Island",
    "SC": "South Carolina",
    "SD": "South Dakota",
    "TN": "Tennessee",
    "TX": "Texas",
    "UT": "Utah",
    "VT": "Vermont",
    "VA": "Virginia",
    "WA": "Washington",
    "WV": "West Virginia",
    "WI": "Wisconsin",
    "WY": "Wyoming",
}


airports_df['state_full'] = airports_df['state'].map(state_abbrev_to_name)
airport_counts = airports_df.groupby('state_full').size().reset_index(name='airport_count')
airports_df = airports_df.merge(airport_counts, on='state_full', how='left')

base = alt.Chart(states_geojson).mark_geoshape(
    fill='transparent',
    stroke='steelblue'
).properties(
    width=800,
    height=400
).project('albersUsa')

color_scale = alt.Scale(scheme='viridis')

airports_chart = alt.Chart(airports_df).mark_circle(size=10, opacity=0.5).encode(
    longitude='longitude:Q',
    latitude='latitude:Q',
    color=alt.Color('airport_count:Q', scale=color_scale),
    tooltip=['name:N', 'city:N', 'state:N']
).project('albersUsa')

choropleth = alt.Chart(airport_counts).mark_geoshape(
    stroke='black'
).encode(
    color=alt.Color('airport_count:Q', scale=color_scale),
    tooltip=['state_full:N', 'airport_count:Q']
).transform_lookup(
    lookup='state_full',
    from_=alt.LookupData(states_geojson, 'properties.name', ['state_full'])
).properties(
    title='Number of Airports by State in the USA'
)

final_map = base + choropleth + airports_chart

final_map

import pandas as pd
import altair as alt
from vega_datasets import data

states_geojson = alt.topo_feature(data.us_10m.url, 'states')
airports_df = data.airports()

state_abbrev_to_name = {
    "AL": "Alabama",
    "AK": "Alaska",
    "AZ": "Arizona",
    "AR": "Arkansas",
    "CA": "California",
    "CO": "Colorado",
    "CT": "Connecticut",
    "DE": "Delaware",
    "DC": "District of Columbia",
    "FL": "Florida",
    "GA": "Georgia",
    "HI": "Hawaii",
    "ID": "Idaho",
    "IL": "Illinois",
    "IN": "Indiana",
    "IA": "Iowa",
    "KS": "Kansas",
    "KY": "Kentucky",
    "LA": "Louisiana",
    "ME": "Maine",
    "MT": "Montana",
    "NE": "Nebraska",
    "NV": "Nevada",
    "NH": "New Hampshire",
    "NJ": "New Jersey",
    "NM": "New Mexico",
    "NY": "New York",
    "NC": "North Carolina",
    "ND": "North Dakota",
    "OH": "Ohio",
    "OK": "Oklahoma",
    "OR": "Oregon",
    "MD": "Maryland",
    "MA": "Massachusetts",
    "MI": "Michigan",
    "MN": "Minnesota",
    "MS": "Mississippi",
    "MO": "Missouri",
    "PA": "Pennsylvania",
    "RI": "Rhode Island",
    "SC": "South Carolina",
    "SD": "South Dakota",
    "TN": "Tennessee",
    "TX": "Texas",
    "UT": "Utah",
    "VT": "Vermont",
    "VA": "Virginia",
    "WA": "Washington",
    "WV": "West Virginia",
    "WI": "Wisconsin",
    "WY": "Wyoming",
}


airports_df['state_full'] = airports_df['state'].map(state_abbrev_to_name)
airport_counts = airports_df.groupby('state_full').size().reset_index(name='airport_count')
airports_df = airports_df.merge(airport_counts, on='state_full', how='left')

base = alt.Chart(states_geojson).mark_geoshape(
    fill='transparent',
    stroke='steelblue'
).properties(
    width=800,
    height=400
).project('albersUsa')

color_scale = alt.Scale(scheme='viridis')

airports_chart = alt.Chart(airports_df).mark_circle(size=10, opacity=0.5).encode(
    longitude='longitude:Q',
    latitude='latitude:Q',
    color=alt.Color('airport_count:Q', scale=color_scale),
    tooltip=['name:N', 'city:N', 'state:N']
).project('albersUsa')

choropleth = alt.Chart(airport_counts).mark_geoshape(
    stroke='black'
).encode(
    color=alt.Color('airport_count:Q', scale=color_scale),
    tooltip=['state_full:N', 'airport_count:Q']
).transform_lookup(
    lookup='state_full',
    from_=alt.LookupData(states_geojson, 'properties.name', ['state_full'])
).properties(
    title='Number of Airports by State in the USA'
)

final_map = base + choropleth + airports_chart

final_map
